	"name": "Dazzling Brilliance Firework",
	"type": "object",
	"img": "icons/magic/fire/explosion-fireball-large-blue.webp",
	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Each creature in the area of effect must make a Constitution saving throw or be [[/condition id=blinded]] until the start of your next turn.</p><p>You can use an action to arm and launch a firework. You can do so a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per short rest. Fireworks have a range of 120 feet, which increases by 30 feet at 5th, 11th, and 17th level. The area of effect is a cylinder with a 10-foot radius and a height of 30 feet, centered on the point of explosion. The radius increases by 10 feet and the height by 30 feet at 5th, 11th, and 17th level. You can choose the radius and height of the cylinder when you launch the firework.</p><p>The DC for all saving throws caused by your fireworks equals your spell save DC.</p>",
